    "text": "It does make sense once you see what else feeds the score. Your HRV is indeed good, 68 ms against a 30-day average of 66.6, but recovery isn't an HRV dial. Two inputs are dragging it to 59%: your resting heart rate is 58 bpm versus a usual 55.4, a meaningful bump given how tight your normal range is, and you're one morning removed from an 80-minute hike that carried a 15.3 training load. Sleep was fine at 425 minutes, about 7.1 h, right on your weekly average. When HRV and resting heart rate disagree like this, the composite hedges toward caution. Practically, treat today as a moderate day, and expect the score to snap back once that heart rate settles.",
